{% extends "base.twig" %}

{% block content %}

<div id="services" class="sub-page-wrap">

  {% include "parent-nav.twig" %}

  <section class="highlight-text child-page">

    {% if post.can_edit %}
    <a class="edit-link" href="{{post.edit_link}}">[Edit me!]</a>
    {% endif %}

    {{post.content}}

    <p>
      <br><a class="button active dark" href="/creative-services/">View Projects</a>
    </p>

  </section>

  <div class="accordion-wrap" id-expander>

    <section class="item-wrap color-1" id-expander-item><!-- add class only-open to make header white and text dark -->

      <article>

        <header class-"expander" id-expander-button>

          <h1>
            Custom Hardware Prototyping &amp; Product Design
          </h1>

          <button><i class="icon-caret-down"></i></button>

        </header>        

        <div class="item-content">

          <!-- <div class="accordion-sub-header">

            <p>
              Integrate latest technology. Works with partners such as: 3M, HP, Intel, LG, PQLabs, Samsung, Zytronic Proven design, work in aluminum. Custom colors, familiar with hydrodipping.
            </p>

          </div> -->

          <div class="text-container">

            <div class="img-row">

              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/hardware/Cust_hard_1.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/hardware/Cust_hard_2.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/hardware/Cust_hard_3.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/hardware/Cust_hard_4.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/hardware/Cust_hard_5.jpg" alt="" title="">

            </div>

            <div class="two-column-text">

              <p>
                As an agile company, Ideum is able to quickly integrate the latest technology as it becomes available. We work with a variety of technology partners, including 3M, HP, Hyundai, Intel, LG, PQLabs, Samsung, Zytronic. We have built custom prototypes for cutting-edge museums and world-class technology companies. In many cases these prototypes have been first-of-their-kind, pushing the boundaries in resolution, touch technology, and integration with complementary technology such as RFID and NFC.
              </p>

              <p>
                Our proven design methods and our ability to rapidly design in aluminum and cold-rolled steel, means that we can produce hardened interactive systems for demanding environments and public spaces. We’ve developed systems with a range of designs and have collaborated with other design firms, architects, and museums to develop custom systems that match the aesthetics of the spaces they are placed in. Along with unique form-factors, we have developed systems in an array of custom colors and textures. We’ve even developed custom etched and hydro-dipped exhibits.
              </p>

            </div>

          </div>

        </div>

      </article>

    </section>

    <section class="item-wrap color-2 " id-expander-item><!-- add class only-open to make header white and text dark -->

      <article>

        <header class-"expander" id-expander-button>

          <h1>
            Application &amp; Exhibit Software Development
          </h1>

          <button><i class="icon-caret-down"></i></button>

        </header>

        <div class="item-content">

          <!-- <div class="accordion-sub-header">

            <p>
              Integrate latest technology. Works with partners such as: 3M, HP, Intel, LG, PQLabs, Samsung, Zytronic Proven design, work in aluminum. Custom colors, familiar with hydrodipping.
            </p>

          </div> -->

          <div class="text-container">

            <div class="img-row">

              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/software/App-Dev_01.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/software/App-Dev_02.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/software/App-Dev_03.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/software/App-Dev_04.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/software/App-Dev_05.jpg" alt="" title="">

            </div>

            <div class="two-column-text">

              <p>
                Ideum has deep roots in user interface design (we’ve been designing exhibits and websites for 15 years). For the last six years, we’ve been at the cutting-edge in developing multitouch and multiuser interactives. More recently we’ve begun to extend our design expertise to include motion tracking, voice recognition, virtual reality and other emerging HCI (human computer interaction) technologies.
              </p>

              <p>
                We are interested in the next generation of multiuser and multimodial experiences. We believe that the best interactive exhibits for museums and public spaces have a strong social component and multi-sensory qualities. New and emerging technologies present new opportunities to illuminate, inspire and engage visitors.
              </p>

              <p>
                Our open and active development process ensures that the software we produce is intuitive. We also work hard to ensure the utmost quality in the code we produce. Our exhibits and websites are easy to update and maintain. Our programmers have experience in a wide-range of software languages. We work in C++, .NET / C#, Python, Java, ActionScript, and a variety of other Web-centric languages.
              </p>

            </div>

          </div>

        </div>

      </article>

    </section>

    <section class="item-wrap color-3" id-expander-item><!-- add class only-open to make header white and text dark -->

      <article>

        <header class-"expander" id-expander-button>

          <h1>
            Responsive Web &amp; Mobile Design
          </h1>

          <button><i class="icon-caret-down"></i></button>

        </header>        

        <div class="item-content">

          <!-- <div class="accordion-sub-header">

