            </p>

          </div> -->

          <div class="text-container">

            <div class="img-row">

              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/responsive/Responsive_01.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/responsive/Responsive_02.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/responsive/Responsive_03.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/responsive/Responsive_04.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/responsive/Responsive_05.jpg" alt="" title="">

            </div>

            <div class="two-column-text">

              <p>
                Ideum’s approach to web and mobile interface design focuses on more than just aesthetics. We find the best way to engage users and encourage participation no matter what device or platform they are connecting from. Ideum's talented designers and developers work together to establish an approach based around usability and the visitor experience. We believe the most effective websites and mobile applications have strong design qualities and focus on functional details to ensure visitor interaction.
              </p>

              <p>
                All of our web and mobile designs are built specifically with responsive design in mind. Whether users are visiting a site on a large, high resolution desktop computer or on a smartphone, Ideum aims to provide them with a beautiful, intuitive experience. Our developers are well-versed in HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, a variety of web programming languages, and can develop native code for iOS and Android.
              </p>

            </div>

          </div>

        </div>

      </article>

    </section>

    <section class="item-wrap color-4" id-expander-item><!-- add class only-open to make header white and text dark -->

      <article>

        <header class-"expander" id-expander-button>

          <h1>
            Technology Planning &amp; Conceptual Design
          </h1>

          <button><i class="icon-caret-down"></i></button>

        </header>        

        <div class="item-content">

          <!-- <div class="accordion-sub-header">

            <p>
              Integrate latest technology. Works with partners such as: 3M, HP, Intel, LG, PQLabs, Samsung, Zytronic Proven design, work in aluminum. Custom colors, familiar with hydrodipping.
            </p>

          </div> -->

          <div class="text-container">

            <div class="img-row">

              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/testing/Tech_planning_1.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/testing/Tech_planning_2.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/testing/Tech_planning_3.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/testing/testing-img4-154x153.jpg" alt="" title="">
              <img src="/wp-content/themes/ideum/images/services/testing/Tech_planning_5.jpg" alt="" title="">

            </div>

            <div class="two-column-text">

              <p>
                Ideum has taken large roles in master planning for technology integration in major museums. In addition, Ideum has been engaged in conceptual design for a variety of interactive exhibitions and exhibits. While our expertise is in technology-based exhibits, we have collaborated in the planning of hands-on physical exhibits, collections, and museum experiences. We strongly believe that technology can create unique and engaging exhibits, but that many of the best exhibitions have a blend of high-tech and traditional experiences.
              </p>

              <p>
                We’ve worked with a wide-range of science museums, planetariums and aquariums, history and cultural institutions, art museums, nonprofits, and companies focused on a variety of topics. This experience, along with our continued work with cutting-edge hardware and modern software techniques, give us a unique perspective when planning for future exhibits and exhibitions.
              </p>

            </div>

          </div>

        </div>

      </article>

    </section>

    {{follow_dialog}}

  </div>

  <br>&nbsp;

